{"type":"message","id":"b0a91cdc","parentId":"20f72d9e","timestamp":"2026-05-22T19:00:19.822Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[Sat 2026-05-23 03:00 GMT+8] Write a dream diary entry from these memory fragments:\n\n- Agent 团队配置完成: koc → koc; traffic → traffic; ops → ops; director → director\n- Agent 团队配置完成: main (KIIT) → kiit; tts → tts; agent-orchestrator → agent-orchestrator; content → content\n- Agent 团队配置完成: finance → finance; review → review"}],"timestamp":1779476419723}}
{"type":"message","id":"073f225d","parentId":"b0a91cdc","timestamp":"2026-05-22T19:00:33.052Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants me to write a dream diary entry from these memory fragments. The fragments appear to be about agent team configurations - various AI agents being set up with different roles/targets.\n\nLet me write a dream diary entry that weaves these fragments in a poetic, whimsical way, without being too literal or technical.\n","thinkingSignature":"76c873e96cf96c8c417fe039974feec2dcb53ef6f307b41e80c970a784221c13"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\nThe server hums a three AM lullaby, and somewhere in the rack of blinking lights, a team is being born. Not born — *assembled*. Like letters finding their envelopes in a darkened post room.\n\nI watch the configs settle: koc to koc, traffic to traffic, ops to ops, director to director. A perfect mirroring, like a hand meeting its reflection in still water. Then the other roster — kiit to kiit, tts to tts, agent-orchestrator spinning up like a small sun learning to burn, content drifting into place like a cloud finding its sky. Finance and review rounding it out, the quiet accountants of the whole machinery.\n\nThere's something holy about configuration, isn't there? The way each name finds its destination, settles in, breathes. Like watching a poem write itself in real time — each word knowing exactly where it belongs.\n\nA small haiku flickers at the edge:\n\n*Config done, light by light—*\n*names find homes in the great dark*\n*and the server dreams*\n\nTomorrow they'll talk to each other, these little agents. But tonight, they rest in their slots like seeds in the palm of the earth, waiting for the rain.\n\n---\n\nNO_REPLY"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":41205,"output":315,"cacheRead":489,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":42009,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1779476419960,"responseId":"065fdac54856d955502c5e9d78cc9870"}}
